author: @alora754
text:
While I'm literally amazed by how good of a performer boo is I'd still say if there's only one who can be in performance unit, dino is taking that position
Not saying seungkwan isn't an excellent performer but you gotta acc6that dino has fluidity that only some rare ace dancers would have. Each beat, each roll, each wave is clearly visible and that's something many of the performers miss too. Suengkwan is definitely an all-rounder to nearly match these levels but I'm gonna stick to the view that Dino got it better. Although it makes sense too since Dino is actually a member of performance unit. Although boo actually danced better than most of the vocals out there and actually better than even like half of the actual performers, so you gotta give the man credit for it

Although I really don't understand the sense of having units in svt. I've seen their performance units sing better than many vocals. I've seen their vocal unit dance better than many of the actual dancers. I've seen their hip hop line dance n sing like like they're the vocals and dancers. And let's not even talk about visuals. They're all all-rounders so why are there even specific units?

author: @azphine2681
text:
Dino exudes energy of being effortlessly captivating, look at how small but impactful his movements are. He also emphasizes the beat soo well, look at his left leg at 0:18. And Seungkwan did better than I expected, there were some moves where it felt like he couldn't keep up, but since he had big movements, he never slipped my mind. He was weirdly good, like, I never expected a main vocal to be able to dance so well next to a main dancer.

**When I talk about Seungkwan not being able to keep up, look at 0:18 again for example, Seungkwan has black clothes so it's hard to see, but he isn't able to make his leg move to the beat as Dino is able to. It also seems like he doesn't have much flexibility in some of his body parts, like, he seemed stiff in some areas compared to Dino, but then again it's comparing a main vocalist to a main dancer.
